title: GitHub-triggered review agents should have a clear comment/reply lifecycle in GitHub threads
---
GitHub webhook-triggered review work should be legible from GitHub itself. Beyond webhook ingress, the system should define how an agent acknowledges `/clawq` commands, reports in-progress review state, posts final PASS/FAIL summaries, and replies back into the correct comment/review thread without spamming or losing continuity. Acceptance criteria: (1) define a GitHub-facing lifecycle for acknowledgment, progress, and final reply; (2) support posting replies/comments back into the correct GitHub thread surface; (3) long-running work has a coherent status strategy (single edited comment, threaded updates, reactions, etc.); (4) behavior is documented and testable.